OL,6,F"This Bolton tram from 1910 is a
OL,7,Fbeautiful tram, but the firm that made
OL,8,Fthat tram no longer exists, so all the
OL,9,Fparts have to be made in Blackpool and
OL,10,Fthey are made here you have to make
OL,11,Fthose parts and that's why this
OL,12,Fbuilding really matters"
OL,14,FThe heritage trams have been described
OL,15,Fas "part of Blackpool's DNA" and the
OL,16,Fcommunity is in agreement that they
OL,17,Fhave an important part in the town's
OL,18,Fidentity.
